frameDefinitions: An Agent manipulates a Fastener to open or close a Containing_object (e.g. coat, jar).
A Useful_location is accessible to some (possibly generic)
An Agent prepares for an Activity. ''
A building or location that can be sealed to prevent entrance, the Locale, ceases to be open for use.
A Process stops at a certain Time and Place.
A Container  is in a state of fullness/emptiness with respect to some Contents.
frameExamples: Mary <t>closed</t> her coat with a belt.
I left the door to the lobby <t>open</t> for you.
The troops were <t>preparing</t> themselves for the mission.
John carried a bucket <t>full</t> of water.
listRoleDefinitions:
This role identifies the item that is closed by the agent with the fastener.
<fex name='Agent'>Lee</fex> <t>buttoned</t> <fex name='Containing_object'>his coat</fex>.
The Agent opens/closes the Containing-object.
This role identifies the fastener that the agent manipulates.
This role identifies the active zone of the container that may be expressed as the direct object of the target verb.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> closes the <fen>Container_portal</fen> or the <fen>Containing_object</fen>.
The location where the closing event takes place.
The <fen>Theme</fen> whose motion is blocked or free.
The place or thing that the <fen>Theme</fen> is headed towards, despite a potential or actual <fen>Barrier</fen>.
An entity that (at least potentially) prevents the <fen>Theme</fen> from getting to the <fen>Useful_location</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Useful_location</fen> is or is not accessible.
An <fen>Agent</fen> prepares for an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Activity</fen> for which an <fen>Agent</fen> is preparing.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> at which an <fen>Agent</fen> prepares for an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where an <fen>Agent</fen> prepares for an <fen>Activity</fen>.
The <fen>Locale</fen> is the entity that ceases to be available for use.
The <fen>Time</fen> of the closure.
The <fen>Place</fen> of the failing locale.
The <fen>Process</fen> which is halting.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
<fen>Container</fen> is used for the entity whose fullness is being described.
<fen>Contents</fen> is used for the stuff that is present/absent in the <fen>Container</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Container</fen> is full.
listRoleExamples: Marcus tied his shoe <fex>with the neon-green shoelaces</fex>.
They close the bank vault <fex>at precisely 5:35PM</fex>.
Shouldn't you have buttoned that <fex>in the bathroom</fex>?
<fex>The other post office</fex> closed so they could build a new one.
The fire department closed <fex>in 2008 </fex> after the city ceased to be incorporated.
Every park closed <fex>in New York City</fex> last week for the fireworks.
